      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LAST FLITE (8) finished second at Young two starts back then did a good job again at her latest appearance over 2000m at Blayney, beaten 2.5 metres into third after being up on the pace. Drawn to enjoy a cosy run but might need things to go her way at some stage. Won't find this any harder and she can get the job done. FOX TROT (10) was unplaced two starts ago then things went amiss last start when he broke and finished 8 metres away in fifth over 1720m at Dubbo. Hard to know where he gets from this slightly awkward draw. This doesn't look as hard so he can bounce back. BILLS SWAN SONG (6) is worth plenty of thought off a last-start win by a head at Dubbo over 2120m. WARRAWEE JACK (2) is in the mix following a fifth at his most recent appearance over 1720m at Young.",
